### 🧠 Alternative: Use Count Parameters

A more efficient way (often used for generating balanced parentheses) is to pass counts of open and close brackets:

```java
public void generateParentheses(int n, List<String> result, String current, int open, int close) {
    if (current.length() == n * 2) {
        result.add(current);
        return;
    }

    if (open < n) {
        generateParentheses(n, result, current + "(", open + 1, close);
    }

    if (close < open) {
        generateParentheses(n, result, current + ")", open, close + 1);
    }
}
```

